Small utility that allows a shell command to be run, captures STDOUT and
STDERR and logs them to STDOUT with timestamp

Examples

$ ./logger.pl ls .
2017-05-07 13:15:07 [18537] STDOUT: logger.pl
2017-05-07 13:15:07 [18537] STDOUT: README
2017-05-07 13:15:07 [18537] STDOUT: README~

$ ./logger.pl find /root
2017-05-08 13:16:02 [18541] STDOUT: /root
2017-05-08 13:16:02 [18541] STDERR: find: `/root': Permission denied

